  "prompt": "How can you use Roku to browse the internet?",
  "response": "Roku devices do not have a built-in web browser like a computer or smartphone. However, there are a few ways to partially browse the internet on a Roku:\n\n1. Screen Mirroring\n- Use screen mirroring from a smartphone or computer to display web content on your Roku\n\n2. Roku Channel Store\n- Some channels offer web-like browsing experiences\n- Examples include YouTube, Facebook, and web video channels\n\n3. Third-Party Apps\n- Some apps like the Puffin TV browser offer limited web browsing\n- These are usually found in the Roku Channel Store\n\n4. Private Streaming Channels\n- Some custom channels might offer web browsing capabilities\n- These require additional setup and are less common\n\n5. Casting\n- Some apps allow casting web content to your Roku device\n- Google Chrome and other casting-enabled browsers can send content\n\nWhile these methods provide some internet browsing capabilities, they are not as comprehensive as using a traditional web browser on a computer or mobile device. Roku is primarily designed for streaming media and entertainment.",
